node.text:
Psychedelic Kelp Forest 🤯 (Trypophobia Warning!) “In ocean photography, low visibility is usually a bad thing. However, I was mesmerized by the kelp forests of Eland's Bay, as they shimmered in and out of view in the cloudy green surf. Eland's Bay is a beach town along South Africa's Atlantic coast, frequented by surfers, dolphins, and sea birds. 

One of the clips from this shoot went viral on TikTok. 30% of the commenters said that they enjoyed it, 30% said that it triggered their trypophobia, 10% thought the kelp looked like dementors from Harry Potter, and 20% said that it reminded them of the psychedelic visuals of an LSD/mushrooms trip 😂.”

What was your reaction when watching this? 🌊

📽 @skypacking #nature
📍Eland's Bay, South Africa
🎶 @sadnightdynamite - Psychedelic Views

node.text:
Tag someone you'd like to be in Petra with👇 Petra is a site at the intersection of natural and cultural heritage forming a unique cultural landscape. Ever since Johann Ludwig Burckhardt aka Sheikh Ibrahim had re-discovered the ruin city in Petra, Jordan, in 1812, the cultural heritage site has attracted different people who shared an interest in the ancient history and culture of the Nabataeans such as travellers, pilgrims, painters and savants. However, it was not until the late 19th century that the ruins were systematically approached by archaeological researchers.

The Ancient city of Petra in Jordan is estimated to be built as early as 5th century BC. Famous for its rock-cut architecture and water conduit system, it is also called the 'Rose City' because of the colour of the stone from which it is carved. It has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1985. In 2001 was added as one of the New 7 Wonders of the World.

Who would you visit this Wonder of the World with? 🤯

📽 @visualsofjulius #nature

A sunset session with @juliagal_ in Mykonos ❤️ Tag someone you would bring here 🌅🇬🇷

Mykonos is an island in the Cyclades group in the Aegean Sea. It's popularly known for its summer party atmosphere. Beaches such as Paradise and Super Paradise have bars that blare thumping music. Massive dance clubs attract world-renowned DJs and typically stay open well past dawn. Iconic landmarks include a row of 16th-century windmills, which sit on a hill above Mykonos town.

📽 @juliagal_ #nature
📍Cavo Tagoo Mykonos, Greece
🎶 Shouse - Love Tonight

node.text:
Norway views from Mt. Bispen ⛰ The views of these Norwegian mountains from top of Bispen (The Bishop) rise steep above the famous Trollstigen road and Isterdalen valley. These mountains attracks climbers, hikers and basejumpers. The prime hiking season is July through September, and you don't have to be a mountain climber to reach the summits. However, a good portion of mountain experience will be useful.

Would you dare to hike this mountain? 👇

📽 @ellisivbrain #nature
📍Mt Bispen, Trollstigen, Norway
